<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-244-369 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 749 351</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 14 1991 v8 n2 p43(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Universal Data Systems cuts prices of high-speed modems.andO;(Universal Data Systems FastTalk V.32)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zimmerman, Michael R.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Universal Data Systems Inc. (Prices and rates).andO;Product:   Universal Data Systems FasTalk (Modem) (Prices and rates).andO;Topic:     ModemsPrice Cutting9600 Bps.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Michael R. ZimmermanandM;Aiming to keep a firm grip on its lead in the V.32 modem market, UniversalData Systems (UDS) last week announced price reductions of as much as 31percent on its line of high-speed modems.andM;UDS lowered the prices of its seven 9,600-bps FastTalk V.32 modems, whichpreviously ranged from $995 to $1,145, to $795 each.andP;  In addition, prices forthe high-end $1,145 V.3225 and its $1,120 rack-mounted version were loweredto $950 and $930, respectively, said company officials.andM;&quot;The big players in the modemandM;industry all learned a hard-taught lesson about price sensitivity and cloneactivity in the 2,400-baud market,&quot; said Larry Cynar, senior industry analystat Dataquest Inc., a market-research firm in San Jose, Calif.andP;  &quot;By doingthis, UDS is saying they're not going to get pushed out by the clone guys.&quot;andM;UDS shipped approximately 60,000 V.32 modems in the United States in 1990,making it the leader in that market, said Cynar.andM;&quot;The time was right to make this move,&quot; said Bill Schlosser, director ofbusiness development at UDS.andP;  &quot;If we didn't do it, someone else was going todo it first.&quot; Schlosser cited the company's use of surface-mount technologyand automated manufacturing processes as two main reasons for the price cuts.andM;&quot;The price reduction is going to make gaining market share extremelydifficult andlsqb;for other vendorsandrsqb;,&quot; said Cynar.andP;  &quot;Because if you can't play theprice game, what other incentive is there to move from one vendor toanother?&quot;andM;UDS, a subsidiary of Motorola Inc., can be reached in Huntsville, Ala., at(205) 430-8000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>